name: What Has Become Of Me? Pt 2 | P0039 #pennydrops
description:
'My name was Hester Rush, a singlewoman. They called me a rogue and vagabond for wandering without means of subsistence. I was sentenced to 14 days hard labor on 24th December 1859. I was 62 years old.'

--

This piece forms part of our artwork for Prison Residences at Shepton Mallet Prison, UK, 18/09/21-03/10/21.
